<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1179,576,598]" box="[151,1179,576,598]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
Type species: 
<taxonomicName authority="Loew" authorityName="Loew" box="[294,556,576,598]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Meromyza" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="africana">
<emphasis box="[294,492,576,598]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Meromyza africana</emphasis>
Loew
</taxonomicName>
(lapsus &amp; unavailable name = 
<emphasis box="[871,1046,577,598]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1830" box="[871,977,577,598]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Meromyza" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Meromyza</taxonomicName>
ZSM).
</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[1052,1172,576,598]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" refId="ref42250" refString="Loew, H. (1860) Bidrag till kannedomen om Afrikas Diptera (part). Ofversigt af Kongliga Fetenskaps-Akademiens Forhandlingar, Stockholm, 17 (2), 81 - 97." type="journal article">Loew, 1860</bibRefCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1436,642,955]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
The genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Andersson" authorityName="Andersson" authorityYear="1977" box="[273,545,642,667]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Meromyzella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[273,418,642,667]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Meromyzella</emphasis>
Andersson
</taxonomicName>
is based upon a single species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Loew. Andersson" authorityName="Loew. Andersson" box="[899,1235,642,667]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Meromyzella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="capensis">
<emphasis box="[899,1032,644,667]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">M. capensis</emphasis>
Loew. Andersson
</taxonomicName>
used for 
<taxonomicName box="[1340,1436,644,667]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Meromyzella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="capensis">
<emphasis box="[1340,1436,644,667]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">capensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the name of 
<taxonomicName authority="Loew" authorityName="Loew" box="[291,458,679,703]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Meromyza" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="africana">
<emphasis box="[291,386,679,703]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">africana</emphasis>
Loew
</taxonomicName>
, which is unavailable and in error for 
<emphasis box="[885,989,679,702]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<taxonomicName box="[885,985,679,702]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Meromyzella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="capensis">capensis</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
The inclusion of 
<taxonomicName authority="Loew, 1860" authorityName="Loew" authorityYear="1860" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Meromyza" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incompleta">
<emphasis box="[1187,1436,678,703]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Meromyza incompleta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[151,283,714,739]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" refId="ref42250" refString="Loew, H. (1860) Bidrag till kannedomen om Afrikas Diptera (part). Ofversigt af Kongliga Fetenskaps-Akademiens Forhandlingar, Stockholm, 17 (2), 81 - 97." type="journal article">
Loew, 
<quantity box="[227,283,714,739]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.724399999999999" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" unit="in" value="1860.0">1860</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in new combination in this genus by 
<bibRefCitation box="[701,944,714,739]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" refId="ref43037" refString="Sabrosky, C. W. (1980) 80. Family Chloropidae. In: Crosskey, R. W., Cogan, B. H., Freeman, P., Pont, A. C., Smith, K. G. V. &amp; Oldroyd, H. (Eds.), Catalogue of the Diptera of the Afrotropical Region. British Museum (Natural History), London, pp. 695 - 712." type="book chapter">Sabrosky (1980: 710)</bibRefCitation>
is a mistake, as Sabrosky has pointed out to me 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[193,346,750,775]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">(comb. orig.)</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Andersson" authorityYear="1977" box="[361,506,750,775]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Meromyzella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[361,506,750,775]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Meromyzella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is included by 
<bibRefCitation box="[679,995,750,775]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" refId="ref41065" refString="Andersson, H. (1977) Taxonomic and phylogenetic studies on Chloropidae (Diptera) with special reference to Old World genera. In: Entomologica scandinavica. 8 (Supplement). Scandinavian Science Press, Klampenborg, pp. 1 - 200." type="book chapter">Andersson (1977: 120â€“131)</bibRefCitation>
in his 
<taxonomicName box="[1072,1220,750,775]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Platycephala" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1072,1220,750,775]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Platycephala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
genus group along with 
<taxonomicName box="[215,360,786,811]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Pachylophus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[215,360,786,811]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Pachylophus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Meigen" authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1830" box="[381,601,786,811]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Meromyza" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[381,498,788,811]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Meromyza</emphasis>
Meigen
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nartshuk" authorityYear="1959" box="[620,799,786,811]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Platycephalisca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[620,799,786,811]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Platycephalisca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[820,968,786,811]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Platycephala" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[820,968,786,811]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Platycephala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1830" box="[989,1067,788,811]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Eurina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[989,1067,788,811]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Eurina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Duda, 1933" authorityName="Duda" authorityYear="1933" box="[1088,1381,786,811]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Trichieurina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1088,1228,786,811]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Trichieurina</emphasis>
Duda, 1933
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Meigen, 1830" authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1830" box="[151,432,822,847]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Camarota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,264,823,846]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Camarota</emphasis>
Meigen, 1830
</taxonomicName>
, all Old World genera, and to which group 
<taxonomicName authority="Duda, 1933" authorityName="Duda" authorityYear="1933" box="[930,1202,822,847]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Paraeurina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[930,1060,823,846]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Paraeurina</emphasis>
Duda, 1933
</taxonomicName>
, a monotypic Italian genus overlooked by Andersson, and the more recently described South African genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Deeming, 1981" authorityName="Deeming" authorityYear="1981" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Archimeromyza" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1143,1318,858,883]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Archimeromyza</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation pageId="31" pageNumber="32" refId="ref41720" refString="Deeming, J. C. (1981) A contribution to the study of afrotropical Chloropine Diptera. Journal of Natural History, 15 (5), 789 - 828. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222938100770581" type="journal article">Deeming, 1981</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Ismay, 1995" authorityName="Ismay" authorityYear="1995" box="[271,546,894,919]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Dudeurina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[271,392,894,919]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Dudeurina</emphasis>
Ismay, 1995
</taxonomicName>
from New Guinea also belong. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Andersson" authorityYear="1977" box="[935,1080,894,919]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Meromyzella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[935,1080,894,919]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Meromyzella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is structurally very similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[151,296,930,955]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Pachylophus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,296,930,955]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Pachylophus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but has a filiform micropubescent arista, and its habits and chosen habitat are similar.
</paragraph>
